data.description: Let's talk!!  This home is priced well below what you could build this home for today!  Sellers want this home sold!  This home is a "show piece".  The popular "Alden" floor plan with tons of upgrades throughout the home include on the exterior, stamped concrete, Dryvit,  stacked stone and a craftsman front door.  Inside you will find 9' ceilings and gorgeous wood vinyl planking. In the kitchen quartz countertops, tile backsplash, farmhouse sink, a huge pantry and black stainless-steel appliances.  In the formal dining room raised panels and coffered ceiling.  The family room offers a cathedral ceiling, gas fireplace with built in shelving on either side and beautiful decorative wood feature from the top of the fireplace to the ceiling, The spacious primary bedroom offers crown molding and pocket doors.  The primary bathroom includes a tile shower and double sinks at a comfort height level. The laundry room is located on the 1st floor with pocket door entry and front load washer and dryer that stay.  Split BR floor plan with 2 spacious guest bedrooms and full bath apart from the primary bedroom. 1st floor covered deck with azek decking is a wonderful place to have your morning coffee or to just enjoy the trees and birds with a good book. Gas line to this deck with gas grill that stays with the property.  Open staircase to the lower level finished family room with walkout patio just adds to the beauty of this home.  1/2 bath in the lower level is also a bonus.  Entertaining is no problem in this home. High efficiency gas furnace with humidifier and superior wall foundation.  This home is a beauty!  Close proximity  to the turnpike, rails to trails, Mt Gretna,  grocery and retail shopping.
